ENTER THREE TRIANGLE VERTICES; INTHE   RANGE OF (0;0) TO (279;159).THEN ENTERSTARTING COORDINATES FOR ATRAVELLER.THE TRAVELLER WILL MOVE AROUND THEHI-RES SCREEN; BOUND BY CERTAINRULES.  A THREE-SIDED DIE ISSIMULATED; AND ITS ROLL CORRESPONDSTO ONE OF THE THREEVERTICES OF THE TRIANGLE.  THETRAVELLERWILL MOVE HALF WAY FROM ITSCURRENTPOSITION TOWARD THE VERTEX SELECTEDBY  THE DIE ROLL.  A COPY OF THETRAVELLER  IS LEFT BEHIND AT ITS OLDPOSITION.  THEPROCESS IS THENREPEATED.  THE PATTERNTHAT EMERGES IS A RECORD OF THETRAVELLER'S JOURNEY AS IT JUMPS FROMPOINT TO POINT.